https://rubymonk.com/learning/books/1-ruby-primer/problems/154-permutations

Number shuffle

Problem Statement:
Given a 3 or 4 digit number with distinct digits, return a sorted array of all the unique numbers that can
be formed with those digits.

Example:
Given: 123
Return: [123, 132, 213, 231, 312, 321]

Tests:
returns [123, 132, 213, 231, 312, 321] for 123
returns [1234, 1243, 1324, 1342, 1423, 1432, 2134, 2143, 2314, 2341, 2413, 2431, 3124, 3142, 3214, 3241, 3412, 3421,
4123, 4132, 4213, 4231, 4312, 4321] for 1234